    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "35efd424_aec770e6",
        "filename": "util/linux/socket.h",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1172779
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-30T21:09:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "For now, it makes my life easier. :)\n\nIt\u0027s probably not infeasible to lift this restriction:\nRecvMsg() can use peeks, allocating increasingly larger control buffers until it\u0027s able to read the entire message without truncation.\n\nSendMsg() is meant to be used after a crash, so it can\u0027t allocate memory, which places the burden on the caller to provide a buffer at least CMSG_SPACE(sizeof(int) * fd_count) sized.\n\nAllowing arbitrarily many file descriptors might be useful in the future (file attachments?), but for now at least, we only ever want to send at most one (and I only allowed multiple descriptors in this iteration to make it easier to test RecvMsg a little more thoroughly).",
      "parentUuid": "2e253d3d_7fbc083a",
      "revId": "6895f1e3db5bf816dfac7a8cf0be61a2d1c46899",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ade279aa_b6b2d918",
        "filename": "util/linux/socket.h",
        "patchSetId": 6
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-04-30T21:11:36Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e For now, it makes my life easier. :)\n\u003e \n\u003e It\u0027s probably not infeasible to lift this restriction:\n\u003e RecvMsg() can use peeks, allocating increasingly larger control buffers until it\u0027s able to read the entire message without truncation.\n\u003e \n\u003e SendMsg() is meant to be used after a crash, so it can\u0027t allocate memory, which places the burden on the caller to provide a buffer at least CMSG_SPACE(sizeof(int) * fd_count) sized.\n\u003e \n\u003e Allowing arbitrarily many file descriptors might be useful in the future (file attachments?), but for now at least, we only ever want to send at most one (and I only allowed multiple descriptors in this iteration to make it easier to test RecvMsg a little more thoroughly).\n\nOK. It’s fair to go with this for now and revisit only if needed.",
      "parentUuid": "35efd424_aec770e6",
      "revId": "6895f1e3db5bf816dfac7a8cf0be61a2d1c46899",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
